HEADWORD: Enascent
<hw>E*nas"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>enascens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>enasci</ets> to spring up;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>nasci</ets> to be born.]</ety> <def>Coming into
being; nascent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp.
Warburton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
